Managing COVID-19
within your fleet
NEW PROCEDURES TO CONSIDER INCLUDING
1.) PERSONAL HYGIENE
AND SANITATION
Provide hand sanitiser at the entrance and exit of
your office. Encourage staff to clean their hands
when coming and going. Include sanitiser in each
vehicle for staff to use during their trips.
2.) KEEP VEHICLE KEYS CLEAN
Keys are handled by many people in a shared fleet.
Ensure they are cleaned after every trip.
Use a damp cloth with antibacterial spray to ensure key
are sanitised between use.
3.) TRACEABILITY
Have a system in place for traceabillity. If a staff
member gets sick, you can easily see which vehicle
they drove.. and which other staff members may
have driven it afterwards.
4.) INTERNAL
COMMUNICATION
Provide clear messaging about procedures to all staff.
This will ensure everyone follows the same set of rules.
Adding localised printed notices to all regular contact
contact points can help reinforce these wider
communications
5.) EDUCATE AND INFORM
Keep abreast of updates from reputable sources.
Educate and share these with staff to ensure they
adhere to your country's Covid- 19 guidelines and
best practices.
6.) ACCESS TO EVERYONE
Consider opening up your fleet to staff that don't
normally have fleet access so that they can mimimise
their risk of infection while travelling for work.
7.) CONSIDER LETTING STAFF USE
THEIR OWN VEHICLES
Give staff the option to use their own vehicles during the crisis
to avoid the risk of transference from using shared vehicles.
Make sure to register any personal vehicles and trips in your
o
pool booking software to enable tracking and attribution of
costs in the future.
BY UPDATING YOUR FLEET GUIDELINES, YOU'LL ENSURE
WE ALL STAY SAFE DURING THESE HARD TIMES.
WE'RE ALL IN THIS TOGETHER.
